>I gave up.
Rookie mistake. Never flat out say your giving up on a story and drop it cold turkey, else you will be seen as a "Unreliable Writer". The trick is to put it on hiatus, say that you hit writers block or want to focus on something else. Put in on hiatus for a year or 2, and everytime someone ask for it, just repeat what you said about you wanted to take a break from it, even put in little beads of hope saying that you have been "thinking about it". Let it slowly drift out of the generals concious and after enouph time has passed, the next time some ask about it just say you abandoned it after years of trying to think of something and your just worn out, and that maybe you will rewrite it in the future. So instead of looking like you just straight up gave up, it looks like you tried your best, but just go exhausted. I done this once with my stories and it works like a charm.
